Package: iridium-browser
Architecture: armhf armel i386 amd64
Pre-Depends: dpkg (>= 1.15.6)
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
	bash,
	libnss3,
	xdg-utils,
	iridium-codecs-ffmpeg-extra (>= 0.6) | iridium-codecs-ffmpeg (>= 0.6)
Recommends: iridium-browser-l10n
Provides: www-browser, iridium-browser-inspector
Replaces: iridium-browser-inspector
Conflicts: iridium-browser-inspector
Description: Iridium browser
 Iridium is a free, open, and libre browser modification of the Chromium code
 base, with privacy being enhanced in several key areas. Automatic transmission
 of partial queries, keywords, metrics to central services inhibited and only
 occurs with consent.
 .
 In addition, all our builds are reproducible, and modifications are auditable,
 setting the project ahead of other secure browser providers.
 .
 This package contains the Iridium browser

