Package: iridium-codecs-ffmpeg-extra
Architecture: armhf armel i386 amd64
Pre-Depends: dpkg (>= 1.15.6)
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Conflicts: iridium-codecs-ffmpeg
Replaces: iridium-codecs-ffmpeg
Description: Extra ffmpeg codecs for the Iridium Browser
 Iridium is a free, open, and libre browser modification of the Chromium code
 base, with privacy being enhanced in several key areas. Automatic transmission
 of partial queries, keywords, metrics to central services inhibited and only
 occurs with consent.
 .
 This package contains the multi-threaded ffmpeg codecs needed for the HTML5
 <audio> and <video> tags. In addition to the patent-free ogg, vorbis and
 theora codecs, aac/ac3/mpeg4audio/h264/mov/mp3 are also included.  See
 iridium-codecs-ffmpeg if you prefer only the patent-free codecs

